Orlando Pirates have appointed Benson Mhlongo as the Club&rsquo;s second Assistant Coach.Pirates Chairman Dr. Irvin Khoza, expressed his delight at giving an opportunity to not only a former Club Captain but most importantly a young South African Coach.&ldquo;It is important for us to move on from the disruption that has necessitated the changes made to the Technical Team. To this end we have also brought in Benson Mhlongo as the second Assistant Coach.&rdquo;&ldquo;With the experience of Augusto Palacious and the enthusiasm of our Assistant Coaches Bradley Carnell and Benson Mhlongo, I am confident that we have a capable Technical Team that can take this team forward, said Dr. Khoza.